==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Resupinate
<hw>Re*su"pi*nate</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>resupinatus</ets>, p. p. of <ets>resupinare</ets> to bend back. See
<er>Resupine</er>.]</ety> <def>Inverted in position; appearing to be
upside down or reversed, as the flowers of the orchis and the leaves of
some plants.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Resupinated</ent>⟦br⟧
